      <title>Assignment 6.2</title>
      <link>https://lapinel-6.course-manager.app/units/unit-66/lessons/lesson-507/files/assignment/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://lapinel-6.course-manager.app/units/unit-66/lessons/lesson-507/files/assignment/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;assignment-62-advanced-data-techniques-prepare&#34;&gt;Assignment 6.2: Advanced Data Techniques (Prepare)&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;goal&#34;&gt;Goal&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Practice working with complex datasets by filtering, sorting, and aggregating data. Visualize the results using &lt;code&gt;matplotlib&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;instructions&#34;&gt;Instructions&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Download or create a dataset with at least &lt;strong&gt;3 columns&lt;/strong&gt; (e.g., names, ages, scores, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Perform the following:&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Filter the data to only include values that meet a condition (e.g., score &amp;gt; 85).&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Sort the data by one column (e.g., by score or age).&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Group the data by a specific field and calculate the average of another field (e.g., average score by age).&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Use &lt;code&gt;matplotlib&lt;/code&gt; to create a &lt;strong&gt;bar chart&lt;/strong&gt; to visualize one of your findings (e.g., student scores).&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Submit your &lt;code&gt;.py&lt;/code&gt; file with the dataset and visualizations to Canvas.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;example-dataset&#34;&gt;Example Dataset&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-python&#34; data-lang=&#34;python&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; pandas &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; pd&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;data &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; {&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;name&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;: [&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;Alice&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;Bob&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;Charlie&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;David&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;],&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;age&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;: [&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;25&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;30&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;35&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;40&lt;/span&gt;],&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;score&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;: [&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;90&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;80&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;85&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;95&lt;/span&gt;]&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;}&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;df &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; pd&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;DataFrame(data)&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;challenge&#34;&gt;Challenge&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Add a second dataset (e.g., &lt;code&gt;age_group&lt;/code&gt; with corresponding &lt;code&gt;score&lt;/code&gt; averages).&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Perform more complex calculations (e.g., median, standard deviation).&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;rubric&#34;&gt;Rubric&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;input disabled=&#34;&#34; type=&#34;checkbox&#34;&gt; Dataset includes at least 3 columns (30%)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;input disabled=&#34;&#34; type=&#34;checkbox&#34;&gt; Filtering, sorting, and aggregation are correctly performed (40%)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;input disabled=&#34;&#34; type=&#34;checkbox&#34;&gt; Visualization is created with &lt;code&gt;matplotlib&lt;/code&gt; (20%)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;input disabled=&#34;&#34; type=&#34;checkbox&#34;&gt; Code runs without errors (10%)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
